<br>
QS doesn't work on nukes.<br>
<br>
Suspend companion isn't a good substitute for pet hold because:<br>
<br>
1. It can't be used if the pet has aggro with any mob<br>
2. It takes 4 seconds to suspend, and another 4 seconds to release<br>
<br>
I consider pet hold ALMOST mandatory on raids. Sure, it's possible if the mage is paying close attention to get by with back off. But most mages I know that take pet control seriously enough to suceed in using pet back off alone to control their pet, also take pet control seriously enough to spend the 6 points for pet discipline. <br>
<br>
Also, many PoP mobs enrage, and if you want your pet to tank enraging mobs (which they can if its slowed; many warriors have trouble tanking unslowed PoP mobs too) you are really going to want pet hold.<br>
<br>
HoE is ok, I guess, in exp groups, although the mob has to survive for 40 seconds (8 second cast, 30 second duration) for the spell to work at full efficiency. On raids HoE has an unacceptably large amount of push. Unless the mob is pinned, you can cause more harm than good with it. <br>
<br>
Conventional wisdom for SCF 3-6 is that it follows a progression like 7%, 9%, 11%, 13%. So the first level is &quot;cheap&quot; and the second two levels are &quot;expensive&quot; and equally so.<br>
<br>
I've heard that agility sucks, but lightning reflexes is awesome. However, to max out LR is a 27 point investment. Good choice... if you have maybe 150 AA...<br>
<br>
My list would be something like:<br>
Run 3<br>
Regen 3<br>
SCM 3<br>
Pet discipline<br>
MC 1<br>
subtelty 1<br>
suspend companion 2<br>
Quick summon 2<br>
EDIT: left out mend companion<br>
SCF 4<br>
subtelety 3<br>
HoE1<br>
ND 1<br>
MC 2<br>
SCF 6<br>
ND 3<br>
<br>
<br>
