 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 924<br> <font color=#333333>(2/11/03 4:27:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Optimal AA path for magicians</span><hr size=1> My AA path does indeed benefit solo and chaining magicians.  They also help those that raid and group.<br>
<br>
I looked at the AA's available when they first came out and tried to figure out what would emphasize efficiency above all else.<br>
<br>
In a group, magicians typically don't have a lot of efficiency problems.  The pets allow sustained damage throughout every fight.  Nukes are icing on the cake, and the mana can be spent whenever you have it to spend.  Basically then, you can adjust your efficiency much more easily in a group than solo.<br>
<br>
An all-magician group is simply a scaled up form of soloing, so that was part of my focus too.<br>
<br>
Because my emphasis was increasing efficiency, I automatically threw out Subtlety, Channeling Focus, Deftness, the combat skills, etc. from Archetype.  They could be had at a later time.  Basically it left Fury, Clarity, and Mastery.  Mastery had the biggest &quot;bang for the buck.&quot;  Clarity's benefit scales inversely with the mana cost of the spells commonly used. Fury's benefit was extremely narrow, only affecting direct damage spells, and only by 7% max, on average.  Mastery maxed affects all spells, and by 15%.<br>
<br>
I looked carefully at the Class skills as well.  Quick Summoning was obvious, as it made chaining safer, and pet canni quicker.  As a side effect, it also made CoTH pulling more doable because it could now be cast in as little as 6 seconds.  Elemental Pact was a little less obvious, but it definitely was a worthwhile skill as well.  I thought long and hard about Improved Reclaim, though.  I knew early on that I would be sacrificing pet canni for mana free pets...... until they introduced Summoning Efficiency as an effect on certain droppable items.  I did the math and discovered I could have the best of both worlds and not have to sacrifice anything.  I could demonstrate my clarity-free mana independence on raids (via pet canni), and I could solo mana free as well, or build successful groups around me and my pets.<br>
<br>
In the end, you could say that I tried to build an AA path that allows a magician the greatest degree of flexibility in fighting styles, both solo and grouped.  Efficiency affects everything.<br>
<br>
To answer your question more directly, there are only very small differences between a magician's solo AA's, grouped AA's, and raid AA's. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A> at: 2/12/03 8:47:24 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2882<br> <font color=#333333>(2/11/03 6:01:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Optimal AA path for magicians</span><hr size=1> I would not claim my path was <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;optimal,&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> but here it is anyway, and my reasoning.<br>
<br>
I am a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;mixed mage,&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with a fair amount of soloing, grouping and raiding.  I mostly group now with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>PoP</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Run 3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is obvious.  After <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Run 2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I got a point of regeneration, but that was probably a mistake.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Regeneration 3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> was obvious during the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Age of Transvergence</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Spell Casting Mastery 1 &amp; 2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> followed, and I should have bought <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>SCM3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> next, but I wanted to play with:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Spell Casting Fury 1 &amp; 2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Crits are fun, and they impress the rubes.  Great pyschological value.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Pet Discipline</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> because it is a must on raids, and it seems obviously a powerful ability.  I have never once regretted getting it as my first class ability.  I depend on it whether soloing, in groups, or on raids.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>SCM 3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> next because I should have done that as soon as possible anyway.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>SCF 3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> because otherwise my points in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>SCF</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> so far were wasted.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Mental Clarity 1</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> because I had two points and could not wait to spend them, and they seemed like a good value for 2 AA.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Quick Summoning 2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Call of the Hero</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, transvergence, and, after 60 levels, chaining and reclaiming pets.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Elemental Pact</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, because chaining and reclaiming pets turns out to be such a great idea.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Quick Summoning 3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, because chaining and reclaiming pets turns out to be such a great idea.  Also, five second pets rule.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Spell Casting Subtlety 3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, because managing aggro became more important to me.  With all the mana I could generate, being able to push the aggro envelope was good.  Again, I am not disappointed in this ability at all.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Improved Intelligence 3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, because then with gear I have 255 intelligence without buffs for tradeskilling.  Also, I am afraid to take the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;IRE leap of faith.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>First Aid 2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, after <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Chromadracs</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> start casting more aggressively, and I was subject to more DOTs soloing.  I do not regret spending 2 AA to be able to bandage up to 70%, although at 63 I almost never bandage.   Also, I was still procrastinating about <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>IRE</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Natural Durability 1</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> because it became available during the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Age of Transvergence</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Finally, I made the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;leap of faith&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and buy <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Improved Reclaim Energy</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Glory be!<br>
<br>
Around this time, the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Great Cataclysm</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> befalls mages, and the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Age of Transvergence</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> comes to a rude end.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Quick Summoning</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Mental Clarity</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are refunded.  I buy back <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Quick Summoning 2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and bank the remaining 11 AA.  I manage to bank 15 AA for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>PoP</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> before its release.<br>
<br>
I ding 61st, and buy <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Fury of Magic 1</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, thinking I can then immediately buy <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>FoM2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Oops.  I decide to keep 9 AA banked to buy <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>FoM2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Host of Elephants</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for when I ding 63rd.<br>
